<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Confessor" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Confessor</orth> (cónfessor and conféssor). 1) a priest who hears confessions: <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.168" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.133" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 133</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.218" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.149" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 149</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.6.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 6, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.3.49" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 49</bibl>.<lb />2) surname of the Anglo-Saxon King Edward: <cit><quote>Edward --'s crown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 88</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>